Sentencas: Protonic ceramic membrane fuel cells (PCMFCs) based on proton-conducting electrolytes have attracted much attention because of many advantages, such as low activation energy and high energy efficiency.
Titulo: High performance protonic ceramic membrane fuel cells (PCMFCs) with Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ perovskite cathode

Sentencas: A stable, easily sintered perovskite oxide BaCe0.5Zr0.3Y0.16Zn0.04O3-delta (BCZYZ) as electrolyte for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC) composite cathode is investigated.
Titulo: High performance protonic ceramic membrane fuel cells (PCMFCs) with Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ perovskite cathode

Sentencas: By fabricating thin membrane BCZYZ electrolyte (similar to 20 mu m) synthesized by a modified Pechini method on NiO-BCZYZ anode support, PCMFCs are assembled and tested by selecting SSC perovskite cathode with high mixed ionic and electronic conductivities.
Titulo: High performance protonic ceramic membrane fuel cells (PCMFCs) with Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ perovskite cathode

Sentencas: An open-circuit potential of 1.015 V. a maximal power density of 528 mW cm(-2), and a low polarization resistance of the electrodes of 0.15 Omega cm(2) is achieved at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: High performance protonic ceramic membrane fuel cells (PCMFCs) with Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ perovskite cathode

Sentencas: The results indicate that BCZYZ proton-conducting electrolyte with SSC cathode is a promising material system for SOFCs.
Titulo: High performance protonic ceramic membrane fuel cells (PCMFCs) with Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ perovskite cathode
